                    </div>
                    <span>THE BEST book I've encountered on programming databases with VB. I've taken a couple of Visual Basic classes over the years but find I'm learning LOTS reading John's book! In fact, some things that were always a bit fuzzy are now very clear.<P>Like another Amazon.com reviewer, I think John needs to do a second edition to this book to cover two topics: more about programming with ADO and programming without a data control. MS Access 2000 doesn't support the DAO so more support for these topics would make a "must-have" book an indispensable reference.<P>As a benefit to his readers, John does provide "updates" to his book via his website. There one can provide feedback, receive monthly update topics, etc.<P>Anyone that wants to UNDERSTAND what and WHY they're doing something when they're programming with databases should buy this book. I only regret it wasn't my textbook for my last VB class.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Personal service, immediate response</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
